dialogueText.dialogue:
 Yes: Believing him will; I'll answer for it, the
Rogue is as unsincere as a First Minister, and would lie
as fast, if he had Language enough to be Intelligible;
but want of that makes all he says neither true nor false;
for Giberidge cannot properly be called either.

 How come you to know that? No more they were;
and that broke off the Match, for they say she was a 
Bastard.

 'Tis generously answer'd. You have my Consent;
now gain her your own way. -- But shall we go in? The
Women talk'd of Tea.

 Nothing, but that I'm glad to be marry'd well;
we Women without a Husband are like Sheep without
a Shepherd, expos'd to Wolves and Foxes.
